This paper focuses on sequence to sequence learning, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses multi-task learning, which is a common technique in machine learning, and explores different settings for sharing encoders and decoders. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions image caption generation, which is a computer vision task, indicating that it could also be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
